# 🤖 AI Knowledge Assistant API

A production-style backend application that integrates Large Language Models (LLMs) into a scalable REST API using Spring Boot.

Built with modern AI engineering practices including Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG), clean architecture, and external API integration.

---

## 🚀 Tech Stack

* Java 17
* Spring Boot
* LangChain4j
* Google Gemini API
* Maven

---

## 📌 Features

* 🔹 AI-powered question answering endpoint
* 🔹 Integration with Google Gemini (LLM)
* 🔹 RESTful API design
* 🔹 Environment-based configuration (secure API key handling)
* 🔹 Clean service-layer architecture

---

## 🧠 How It Works

1. Client sends a question via HTTP request
2. Spring Boot controller receives the request
3. Service layer forwards prompt to Gemini API via LangChain4j
4. AI-generated response is returned to the client

---

## 📡 API Endpoints

### Ask a Question

GET /ai/ask?q=your_question_here

**Example:**
/ai/ask?q=Explain%20Spring%20Boot

---

## ⚙️ Setup Instructions

### 1. Clone the repository

git clone https://github.com/your-username/ai-knowledge-assistant-api.git

### 2. Set environment variable

export GEMINI_API_KEY=your_api_key_here

### 3. Run the application

mvn spring-boot:run

